00:48.166 --> 00:51.502
<i>Forging an intelligence file</i>
<i>is always tricky.</i>

00:51.570 --> 00:54.805
<i>Spies are trained to catch</i>
<i>even tiny inconsistencies,</i>

00:54.873 --> 00:56.340
<i>from outdated typeface</i>

00:56.408 --> 00:59.009
<i>to the wrong kind</i>
<i>of thermochromatic ink.</i>

00:59.077 --> 01:00.845
<i>Even the folder needs</i>
<i>to be picture-perfect,</i>

01:00.912 --> 01:02.413
<i>because the fact is,</i>

01:02.480 --> 01:05.215
<i>spies</i> do <i>judge books</i>
<i>by their covers.</i>

01:05.283 --> 01:06.383
So, here's the story.

01:06.451 --> 01:08.252
This report came
from a Navy buddy

01:08.320 --> 01:09.653
who's serving in Japan,

01:09.721 --> 01:11.488
where they still use
the old-school Pentagon folders.

01:11.556 --> 01:13.557
And I happened
to have one.

01:13.625 --> 01:15.526
So, thank God
for government inertia, huh?

01:15.594 --> 01:18.195
But Jesse's been working
on this investigation for years.

01:18.263 --> 01:19.663
Well, everything
<i>he</i> was looking into

01:19.731 --> 01:21.098
and all the stuff
<i>we</i> found --

01:21.166 --> 01:22.733
this little baby
connects all the dots.

01:22.801 --> 01:24.501
It's your masterwork, Sam.

01:24.569 --> 01:25.803
I owe you mojito.
Damn straight.

01:25.871 --> 01:28.405
Before we start
patting ourselves on the back,

01:28.473 --> 01:30.674
can we talk about
what we're doing to Jesse?

01:30.742 --> 01:32.076
Fi, Jesse's seen a <i>lot</i>
<i>of bad things happen</i>

01:32.143 --> 01:33.377
to a <i>lot</i> of good people.

01:33.445 --> 01:34.678
He just wants a name,

01:34.746 --> 01:35.946
and we're just gonna give him
that name.

01:39.251 --> 01:41.652
"John Barrett."

01:41.720 --> 01:42.820
God, why didn't I
put this together?

01:42.888 --> 01:43.854
John Barrett.

01:45.490 --> 01:47.224
It's great cover running
a telecom conglomerate.

01:47.292 --> 01:49.627
It gets Barrett into
every corner of the globe.

01:49.694 --> 01:51.362
Massive resources, highest level
government access.

01:51.429 --> 01:52.429
It's a nice perch
for a guy

01:52.497 --> 01:53.764
looking to start
a few little wars

01:53.832 --> 01:54.498
and make a buck
off it.

01:54.566 --> 01:55.966
This is...

01:56.034 --> 01:57.601
I mean, I was looking
at private military companies,

01:57.669 --> 01:58.602
arms dealers,
retired spooks.

01:58.670 --> 02:00.004
I should've been...

02:00.071 --> 02:02.606
Watching the guy
who was laying the phone lines.

02:02.674 --> 02:04.475
Where do I send
my "thank you" note?

02:04.542 --> 02:06.143
Oh, a buddy of mine
stationed in Japan.

02:06.211 --> 02:07.945
He, uh, didn't even know
what he had there.

02:08.013 --> 02:10.146
All right, man.

02:10.215 --> 02:11.582
Drake Tech's based
in New York, right?

02:11.650 --> 02:12.716
Let's head up there,

02:12.784 --> 02:14.385
let Barrett know
his number's up.

02:14.452 --> 02:15.853
Why go to where
he's strongest?

02:15.921 --> 02:17.187
We have what he wants.

02:17.255 --> 02:18.956
Better to make him
come to us.

02:19.024 --> 02:20.624
What, do you want
to call him up,

02:20.692 --> 02:22.693
let him know he's got a bible
he's been looking for?

02:22.761 --> 02:24.328
Yep. That's exactly
what <i>I</i> was thinng.

02:27.098 --> 02:28.666
What?

02:28.733 --> 02:30.067
I'm having friends over
to play cards.

02:30.135 --> 02:31.168
It's my turn to host.

02:32.337 --> 02:33.771
Oh, that must be Suzie.

02:33.838 --> 02:35.973
Uh, well, I guess it's time
to go someplace

02:36.041 --> 02:37.942
where you won't be interrupted
by Canasta.

02:41.246 --> 02:42.813
Three years.

02:42.881 --> 02:45.649
It's over a thousand days, man.
Here it is.

02:45.717 --> 02:46.817
Are you sure about this?

02:46.885 --> 02:48.319
You sure you want to
play it straight?

02:48.386 --> 02:49.286
Well, there's no point
lying to a man

02:49.354 --> 02:50.688
with Barrett's resources.

02:50.755 --> 02:53.257
We're just two burned spies
selling a book code.

02:53.325 --> 02:54.325
You ready?

02:55.627 --> 02:56.593
Yes.

03:03.168 --> 03:04.234
Hello?

03:04.302 --> 03:05.636
Mr. Barrett.
Michael Westen.

03:05.704 --> 03:08.005
Sorry to bother you
on your private line,

03:08.073 --> 03:10.641
but I have
this odd-looking bible.

03:10.709 --> 03:12.109
I've been flipping
through it,

03:12.177 --> 03:14.178
and it appears to be
a book code.

03:14.245 --> 03:16.080
Is that at all interesting
to you?

03:19.250 --> 03:21.251
Can you please
excuse me?

03:21.319 --> 03:23.020
This'll just take a sec.

03:32.197 --> 03:34.531
My wife doesn't even
have this number.

03:34.599 --> 03:35.733
How'd you get it?

03:35.800 --> 03:37.401
You want to talk
about your wife

03:37.469 --> 03:39.136
not having
your unlisted number

03:39.204 --> 03:41.205
or the book code
you've been robbing banks

03:41.272 --> 03:42.506
and killing people
to find?

03:42.574 --> 03:43.974
Who is this?

03:44.042 --> 03:45.442
I used to work
for the government.

03:45.510 --> 03:46.510
So did my partner,

03:46.578 --> 03:47.644
Jesse Porter.

03:47.712 --> 03:48.779
Now we're working
freelance.

03:48.847 --> 03:50.247
Thought
you might be hiring.

03:50.315 --> 03:52.216
And just what is it
you boys think I do?

03:52.283 --> 03:54.218
Don't waste our time,
Mr. Barrett.

03:54.285 --> 03:55.586
You're a merchant
of death.

03:55.653 --> 03:57.021
And business is booming.

03:57.088 --> 03:58.422
You have
the wrong number, son.

03:58.490 --> 04:00.758
And you have the wrong man.

04:00.825 --> 04:03.260
I run a telecom company.

04:07.599 --> 04:09.066
Well, the bible's here
in Miami.

04:09.134 --> 04:10.968
Whenever you're ready to talk,
let us know.

04:16.374 --> 04:17.940
That could have
gone better.

04:18.009 --> 04:19.910
Well, it went as well
as it needed to.

04:19.978 --> 04:21.879
All right.
Barrett wants the bible.

04:21.946 --> 04:24.381
If he can't deal for it,
he'll try to steal it.

04:24.449 --> 04:28.085
A man like that,
he's already tracking us down.

04:29.454 --> 04:31.188
Yeah.

04:34.144 --> 04:35.264
